{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778713444,"nonce":"xF13aadi4Mi78i1nlgfAMQY6t9U=","title":"RunPod runbook: specify ~/.local/bin/ as install location for runpodctl","message":"## Problem\n\nThe RunPod runbook in `CLAUDE.md` (§1 Prerequisites) says:\n\n\u003e `runpodctl` binary from GitHub releases (the `install.sh` requires sudo; download the binary manually if sudo is unavailable).\n\nIt doesn't say *where* to install the binary. On 2026-05-12 a session followed this instruction and put `runpodctl` under `~/.dotfiles/bin/`. That directory is for *tracked* dotfiles scripts, not for downloaded third-party binaries — and any untracked file there then trips dotfiles' pre-auth-check (`3f57688`) and blocks auth-merges.\n\n## Fix\n\nUpdate §1 to specify the install location explicitly:\n\n\u003e `runpodctl` binary from GitHub releases. Install to `~/.local/bin/runpodctl` (already on PATH; reserves `~/.dotfiles/bin/` for tracked scripts). The `install.sh` requires sudo; if unavailable, download the binary manually and `chmod +x`.\n\n## Cross-refs\n\n- Surfaced during dotfiles auth-failure `fd02096c` (2026-05-13), where `?? bin/runpodctl` blocked merge.\n- Related: `3f57688` (auth-merge incorrectly fails on untracked files) — fixing that would mitigate the symptom, but specifying the install location avoids the foot-gun entirely.","files":null}]}